codex
The new standalone Python rerank surface is exposed but will be identity in the configured Python builds because the engine reranker feature is not enabled. It also accepts non-finite scores into ranking math, so the public API can return invalid scores instead of validating malformed input.

Full review comments:

- [P1] Enable reranker feature for Python builds — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:1277-1279
  In the normal Python build path, `src/python/pyproject.toml` only enables `pyo3/extension-module` and `default-embedder`, and `fathomdb-py` does not forward `fathomdb-engine/default-reranker`. That means this new public `fathomdb.rerank(..., rerank_depth>0)` call reaches the feature-off `rerank_fused` implementation and returns identity instead of loading/running the CE, so the advertised Python/Slice-5 standalone reranker silently never reranks unless someone builds with an extra dependency feature manually.

- [P2] Reject non-finite passage scores — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:1239-1241
  For callers that pass `float('nan')` or infinities as `score`, `extract::<f64>()` succeeds and the value flows into the rerank normalization/sort, which can produce NaN blended scores or unstable ordering rather than the typed validation error promised for malformed passages. Please check `score.is_finite()` after extraction and raise `WriteValidationError` when it is not finite.
